GreenFest  Competition

Students interested in participating in GreenFest  Competition must submit an online application by  p.m PERIOD on Friday Feb PERIOD  to the San Diego State GreenFest website PERIOD In addition members must attend a mandatory meeting from   p.m PERIOD on Feb PERIOD  in Aztec Mesa  PERIOD Each group must have at least  members to qualify PERIOD There are eight challenges worth as much as  points PERIOD Groups may choose which events they wish to participate in when applying PERIOD The events include a boat challenge Sustain Your Roots a fashion show a music video a keynote speaker address Green Thursday and a Farmers Market event PERIOD To register a group or read more details about the competition and challenges visit as.sdsu.edugreenfestspirit.php PERIOD



A.S PERIOD Election WriteIns

Although the formal deadline for applying for an Associated Student position passed students interested in running for a position may still do so if and only if they are written in PERIOD These students are required to submit a candidate application to the A.S PERIOD Government Affairs Office located on the second floor of the Parma Payne Goodall Alumni Center PERIOD Candidates must bring their Red ID PERIOD For more information visit as.sdsu.edugovtelection or contact the A.S PERIOD elections coordinator at aselectionsmail.sdsu.edu PERIOD
